  "prompt": "Why does Quora do this \"marked as needing improvement?",
  "response": "On Quora, the \"marked as needing improvement\" status typically occurs when:\n\n1. The answer is considered low quality by the community\n2. It doesn't meet Quora's content standards\n3. Contains grammatical errors\n4. Lacks sufficient detail or clarity\n5. Seems potentially inaccurate or incomplete\n\nThis feature allows the Quora community and moderators to flag answers that need editing or refinement. The goal is to maintain high-quality, informative content on the platform. Users can improve their answer to remove this status by:\n\n- Adding more details\n- Correcting grammar and spelling\n- Providing better sources\n- Expanding on the explanation\n- Making the answer more comprehensive\n\nIt's a community-driven quality control mechanism designed to ensure that answers meet certain standards of quality and usefulness.",
